Package: lotusd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - daemon
 Lotus is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Lotus uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Lotus Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides the daemon, lotusd, and the CLI tool
 lotus-cli to interact with the daemon.

Package: lotus-qt
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer network based digital currency - Qt GUI
 Lotus is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Lotus uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Lotus Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides Lotus-Qt, a GUI for Lotus based on Qt.

Package: lotus-tx
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: peer-to-peer digital currency - standalone transaction tool
 Lotus is an experimental new digital currency that enables anonymous, instant
 payments to anyone, anywhere in the world. Lotus uses peer-to-peer
 technology to operate with no central authority: managing transactions
 and issuing money are carried out collectively by the network. Lotus Core
 is the name of the open source software which enables the use of this currency.
 .
 This package provides lotus-tx, a command-line transaction creation
 tool which can be used without a lotus daemon.  Some means of
 exchanging minimal transaction data with peers is still required.
